# Intake — KS Global Estates

## Brief

Encoded structured requirements for downstream validation.

**Slug:** `ks-global-estates`

**Client:** KS Global Estates (Global Real Estate / Luxury Properties)

**Posting Summary:** "KS Global Estates is seeking a qualified web developer or agency to design and develop a professional website. The project involves creating a visually appealing and user-friendly site that effectively communicates our brand and services. The ideal candidate will have experience in web design and development, with a strong portfolio showcasing previous work. We are looking for someone who can deliver high-quality results within a reasonable timeframe and budget."

### Explicit Requirements (Acceptance Criteria)

| # | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|-------------|-------------------|
| 1 | **Professional frontend + backend website** | Full-stack application with real or mock backend architecture; both frontend and backend functional on first paint |
| 2 | **Visually appealing design** that communicates brand and services | Cohesive, distinctive visual identity; color palette, typography, and layout intentional and on-brand for luxury real estate; zero cookie-cutter elements |
| 3 | **User-friendly interface and experience** | Intuitive navigation, logical information hierarchy, responsive desktop + mobile, no cognitive friction |
| 4 | **Mock database of real estate properties** | 20–30+ properties seeded (houses, condos, estates, penthouses, global locations); property data includes name, type, location, price, beds/baths, sqft, images, details |
| 5 | **List view for property browsing** | All properties visible in a filterable, sortable list; clicking a property shows details; updates in real-time when filters/sorts applied |
| 6 | **Map view for property discovery** | Interactive Leaflet map with OpenStreetMap tiles; properties displayed as clickable map markers with price pins or custom icons; map syncs with list in real-time; no console errors on first paint |
| 7 | **Synchronized list-map interaction** | Filtering, sorting, or searching in list updates map immediately; clicking map pin highlights/opens corresponding list item; clicking list item centers/highlights map pin and shows detail |
| 8 | **Property imagery only** (no unrelated stock) | All property images are houses, condos, estates, interiors, skylines, or luxury property-related; no generic stock photography or filler images |
| 9 | **Design must NOT appear AI-generated** | Deliberately avoids known AI-site tell-tales: no generic centered hero + three-icon feature row, no purple/indigo gradient blobs, no Lorem/filler copy, no cookie-cutter Inter-everywhere type, no identical rounded cards in rigid grids, no fake logo strips, no emoji bullets, no symmetric "AI slop" spacing; instead, bespoke luxury design with asymmetric/editorial layouts, distinctive typography, intentional whitespace, refined motion, specific brand palette |
| 10 | **Production-quality feature richness (10/10)** | Multiple real working features beyond a prototype: faceted filtering (price, beds/baths, type, location, sqft, status), sorting, map-list sync, property detail pages with image galleries, favorites/saved properties (persisted), responsive design, polished interactions; NOT a minimal 1-5/10 demo |
| 11 | **High-quality portfolio work** | Code is clean and well-structured; design is bespoke and deliberate; no em or en dashes in UI, cover letter, or deck; responsive and performant on desktop and mobile; no console errors on first paint |

### Design Direction

**Aesthetic:** Premium Global Real Estate — inspired by luxury property marketing and editorial design (NOT michaelwegter.com's portfolio palette)

**Key Anti-AI Directives:**
- NO generic centered hero sections
- NO purple/indigo gradient blobs
- NO "Lorem ipsum" or filler copy
- NO cookie-cutter rounded-card grids (3-col rigid layout)
- NO excessive Inter/system-font everywhere
- NO fake logo strips
- NO emoji bullets or pseudo-social proof
- YES asymmetric/editorial layouts, distinctive type pairings, real content, intentional whitespace, refined micro-interactions

**Design System (TBD by Planner):**
- Primary Palette: Sophisticated neutrals (charcoal, cream, soft grays) + one or two luxury accent colors (gold, deep teal, matte black) — refined and timeless
- Typography: Editorial serif or slab for headlines (e.g., Playfair, Fraunces) + humanist sans for body (e.g., Inter, Sohne, Graphik)
- Texture/Mood: Minimal, editorial, uncluttered; breathing room; property images as hero content
- Motion: Subtle, intentional; hover states that feel responsive, not decorative

### Build Scope

**Richness Level:** 10/10 → Genuinely full-featured, production-quality app with several real working features

**Hero Feature:** Synchronized split-view Leaflet map (with custom price-pin markers, hover/click sync, clustering or fly-to) beside a live, filterable property listings grid — filtering, sorting, searching update both map and list in real-time; clicking a pin opens a rich property detail view with image gallery and inquiry form

**Supporting Features:**
1. **Faceted Filtering:** price range, beds/baths, property type (house/condo/estate/penthouse), city/country, sqft range, listing status
2. **Sorting:** by price, newest, type, sqft, distance (if applicable)
3. **Full-Text Search:** search property names, locations, or descriptions
4. **Favorites / Saved Properties:** click to save; persists in localStorage; separate favorites view
5. **Property Detail Pages:** full image gallery with carousel, amenity list, location map embed, price and specs, description, inquiry/contact form (CTA)
6. **Responsive Design:** mobile-first; all features work on mobile, tablet, desktop

**Out of Scope:** Advanced analytics, social sharing, agent profiles, mortgage calculators, advanced route planning

### Technology Stack

**Maps:**
- Primary: Leaflet.js + OpenStreetMap tiles (proven from mn-state-park-tracker; no API key dependency)
- Markers: Custom price-pin markers or clustering; hover/click events sync to list
- Constraint: Map MUST render on first paint; zero console errors

**Backend:**
- Approach: Mock property DB (realistic for this environment) — can be seeded JSON or a Flask blueprint with mock data
- If Flask blueprint: run locally during dev, point deployed build at `https://api.michaelwegter.com/ks-global-estates/properties` (or equivalent prefix)
- If pure frontend: mock data embedded in JS or loaded from static JSON file
- Data model: each property = { id, name, type, location, lat/lng, price, beds, baths, sqft, images[], description, amenities[] }
- Favorites: localStorage with property ID array

**Imagery:**
- Property images sourced from free stock (Unsplash, Pexels, Pixabay) filtered for houses, condos, estates, luxury interiors only
- All imagery relevant to real estate; ZERO generic or unrelated stock

**Persistence:**
- Favorites/saved searches: localStorage (no backend required)
- Page state: React state or vanilla JS; filter/sort state does not need to persist across sessions for MVP

**Responsive:**
- Mobile-first design; breakpoints for tablet and desktop
- Map may stack or scale based on viewport

### Hard Gates (Acceptance)

1. Every requirement (1–11) visibly addressed in demo AND mentioned in cover letter
2. Map renders Leaflet + OSM on first paint with zero console errors
3. All 20–30 properties visible on map and in list
4. Filter/sort/search updates both map and list in real-time
5. Clicking map pin highlights list item and opens detail; vice versa
6. Property detail page displays image gallery, specs, and inquiry CTA
7. Favorites system works (add/remove, persists in localStorage)
8. Design is bespoke, visually distinctive, and deliberately avoids AI tells (no gradient blobs, generic grids, filler copy, etc.)
9. Property imagery only (no unrelated stock)
10. Responsive on mobile, tablet, desktop; no console errors on first paint
11. Zero em or en dashes anywhere (UI, cover letter, deck)
12. Live `/demos/ks-global-estates/` route loads locally with full functionality; deployed version at `https://michaelwegter.com/demos/ks-global-estates/` after `git push` (verified via push confirmation, not live poll)

### Constraints

- **Feature scope:** 1 hero (map-list sync) + 5–6 supporting features (filter, sort, search, favorites, detail, responsive)
- **Property count:** 20–30 realistic listings minimum
- **File budget:** ≤20 demo files (inclusive of images)
- **Build time:** ≤5 minutes local build + ≤2 minutes map/list interactive smoke test
- **Typography:** No em or en dashes anywhere
- **Design:** Bespoke only; zero reuse of michaelwegter.com theme, components, or portfolio palette
- **Imagery:** Property-only; 100% real estate related
- **Map tiles:** Leaflet + OpenStreetMap (no Mapbox token)

### Risks & Notes

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|
| Vague client brief (no budget/timeline/pages) | Treat orchestrator startup brief as the canonical requirement set; brief.json captures all stated and inferred needs; cover letter references each explicitly |
| No confirmed KS Global Estates brand assets (logo, palette, fonts) | Researcher confirms whether KS GE has a live site or brand identity; if none, planner invents a credible bespoke luxury identity and notes it in the demo intro |
| Anti-AI design is subjective | Researcher gathers concrete tell-tale signs (gradient blobs, cookie-cutter cards, pseudo-content patterns) and planner deliberately excludes each; design review flags any suspicious patterns |
| Property imagery sourcing and consistency | Researcher curates a cohesive set of 20–30 high-quality house/condo/estate images; planner applies consistent filters (color grade, aspect ratio, mood) for visual unity |
| Leaflet map rendering performance at scale | Leaflet with OSM tiles + 20–30 markers is trivial; no performance risk; test clustering or simple marker layer |
| List-map sync complexity | Standard React state or vanilla JS event binding; sync pattern proven in mn-state-park-tracker; low risk |
| Responsive design on mobile for map | Leaflet is mobile-aware; use CSS grid/flex to stack or side-scroll map on small viewport; test on real mobile or DevTools |
| Deployed build pointing to correct API base | If using Flask blueprint, dev build points at `http://localhost:5000/ks-global-estates/...`; deployed build points at `https://api.michaelwegter.com/ks-global-estates/...` via environment variable or conditional base URL; mock fallback ensures local preview always works |
| Live URL verification disabled from this environment | Verify locally: build, run `npx serve` or Vite preview, Playwright against `http://localhost:...`, full smoke test. Deploy via `git push` (confirm push succeeded). State plainly in cover letter that live verification not possible from this machine; trust the auto-deploy mechanism |

## handoff

- **Produced:** `brief.json` with 11 explicit requirements + implicit needs + 3 demo concepts; structured requirements table with acceptance criteria; anti-AI directives explicit; design direction and tech stack defined.
- **Decision:** Hero = synchronized Leaflet map + filterable listings grid over 20–30 mock-property DB; 10/10 feature richness; bespoke luxury design deliberately avoiding AI tells; property imagery only; Leaflet + OpenStreetMap (no API key); mock backend or Flask blueprint.
- **Next needs (researcher):** Gather AI tell-tale checklist (gradient blobs, cookie-cutter grids, pseudo-content, symmetric spacing, etc.) and concrete avoidance strategies; pull luxury real estate visual conventions (editorial design, refined palettes, asymmetric layouts); curate 20–30 property images (houses, condos, estates, interiors, skylines) all high-quality and on-brand; confirm KS Global Estates existing brand assets or note that identity is invented bespoke.
- **Next needs (planner):** Design a bespoke luxury palette (hex values), editorial font pairing (Google Fonts), and asymmetric component library that deliberately avoids AI tells; sketch map + list split layout; define filter/sort/search UX; clarify property detail modal design; specify favorites interaction; confirm responsive breakpoints.
- **Risks:** Brief is vague (no budget/timeline in posting); no confirmed brand assets (mitigated by bespoke invention); live URLs unverifiable from this environment (all verification local; deploy via push + trust).
- **Constraint:** Leaflet + OSM tiles (no Mapbox token), zero console errors on first paint, property imagery only, no em/en dashes anywhere, GitHub handle mwegter95, design must fit global luxury real estate (not michaelwegter.com portfolio palette).
